The course deals with Spanish lexicology and to a lesser extend with semantics and lexicography.
The second part of the course is focused on the syntax of the Spanish language. It includes a theoretical overview of the main syntactic categories and functions  as well as exercises in syntactic analysis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to introduce the students to the lexicology of the Spanish language, and to a lesser extend to lexicography and semantics. The course will deal with practical issues as well as more practical ones. The practical part will be specially interesting for L2 speakers of Spanish. The purpose of the second part of the course is to provide the students with knowledge of the main syntactic categories and functions in Spanish, and skills for applying theoretical knowledge in the syntactic analysis of sentences in Spanish.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course the students: 1) are aquainted with the basic concepts of lexicology and different aspects of Spanish vocabulary; 2) are acquainted with the very basics of semantics and lexicography; 3) have knowledge of the main syntactic categories and functions in Spanish and are able to apply this knowledge in the syntactic analysis.
